  "text": "We previously showed that UA suppressed growth of HepG2 HCC cells [CITATION_1] . In order to prove if this was the case in other HCC cell types, we further tested the effect of UA on the proliferation in other HCC cell lines. As shown in Fig. 1a , UA inhibited proliferation of Bel-7402 HCC cells in the dose-dependent manner with a significant inhibition observed at 25-30 μM ranges of UA treatment starting at 24 and up to 72 h as determined by MTT assays. The IC50 was 23.067 μM. Similar results were also observed in other HCC cell lines (Fig. 1b) . We next performed the cell cycle experiment. As expected, compared with the untreated control cells, UA significant increased the proportion of cells at G0/G1 phase (>19 %), while the proportion of cells at S phases were reduced (Fig. 1c) suggesting that UA induced cell cycle arrest in G0/G1 phase in Bel-7402 cells.",
